occurrenceRemarks: We were birding in the Acadia Trail Park in Fort Worth, Texas and observing birds in a wooded area when they all flew off rapidly at the same time.  So we started looking for the Hawk that caused the birds to flee and it flew into the trees and perched real close to us.  I could not get a shot without branches in the way.

occurrenceRemarks: Most likely the same hawk I posted previously, January 22nd. Very confident is sharp-shinned but looking for confirmation.  Reasons I believe is sharp-shinned; Dark back of neck, skinny legs, wide chest, tail appears to have sharp corners, looks slightly larger than mourning dove.
